definition: produced locally/local product (with distinctive native features)
earth/dust/clay/local/indigenous/crude opium/unsophisticated/one of the eight categories of ancient musical instruments 八音[ba1 yin1]

sentences.english: Dried persimmon is one of the characteristic local products in Licheng.
sentences.chinese: 柿饼是黎城县特色土产之一。

sentences.english: He made him ride on the high places of the earth, that he might eat the increase of the fields;
sentences.chinese: 耶和华使他乘驾地的高处，得吃田间的土产。

sentences.english: They ate the corn and other food that had been harvested in the land of Canaan.
sentences.chinese: 但在吉甲开始，他们便可以吃迦南地所出的一切土产。

sentences.english: Jade is a famous native product of china.
Again he prayed, and the heavens gave rain, and the earth produced its crops.
sentences.chinese: 他又祷告，天就降下雨来，地也生出土产。

sentences.english: And for thy cattle， and for the beast that are in thy land， shall all the increase thereof be meat.
sentences.chinese: 这年的土产也要给你的牲畜和你地上的走兽当食物。

sentences.english: And for the wood offering, at times appointed, and for the firstfruits.
sentences.chinese: 我又派百姓按定期献柴，和初熟的土产。

sentences.english: Honour the LORD with thy substance, and with the firstfruits of all thine increase
sentences.chinese: 你要以财物，和一切初熟的土产，尊荣耶和华。
